Andrew Boyce: Scunthorpe defender joins Notts County on loan
Notts County have signed Scunthorpe United defender Andrew Boyce on loan for the rest of the season.Boyce, 26, has only made one appearance for the Iron this season, in the FA Cup against Southend in November, but played nine games whileon loan at Hartlepoolearlier in the season.Notts boss Jamie Fullarton said: "Boyce brings physicality and he has a hugely strong presence."He's a leader and I am happy he has chosen to sign for Notts County."Find all the latest football transferson our dedicated page.